New Records: David Wiese blasted 13 runs in Namibia’s super over total of 21
Ruben Trumpelmann bagged four wickets, including two with his first two balls
Key Match Events: Namibia beat Oman in the super over
David Wiese starred with bat and ball as Namibia beat Oman in the super over
The match at Kensington Oval went to a super over after a nerve-jangling low-scoring battle
Ruben Trumpelmann skittled Oman for 109 all out in 19.4 overs
Zeeshan Maqsood played a good knock of 22 for his side
Namibia’s run-chase faltered after a stunning bowling performance by Oman’s Mehran Khan
Pre-Game Insights: Matthew Hayden at the pitch report says that there is a bit of wind coming in from the East coast and in general, the boundaries are small all across the ground
Eion Morgan says that the pitch will get slower as the game goes on and the pacers will use the slower balls more and more
Post-Match Reflections: David Wiese was the hero for the Africans, blasting 13 runs in Namibia’s super over total of 21 before then restricting Oman to 10 runs to seal victory
Miscellaneous Highlights: The boundaries are small all across the ground
